From: qinf-build <build@qinf.local>
Subject: [PATCH] qinf: add ggml_deltanet_pre_state Metal backend (Phase 4)

PR 4.2.B — qinf downstream patch.

Adds the Metal backend for GGML_OP_DELTANET_PRE_STATE: the fused kernel
itself (kernel_deltanet_pre_state_f32 in ggml-metal.metal), the
dispatch case + ggml_metal_op_deltanet_pre_state op function, the
supports_op gate, the pipeline lookup, and the kargs struct.

This is the GPU half of the op introduced by 0004. Constraints:
  - F32 dst + all srcs
  - src0/src1 dim-0 stride == sizeof(float) (rows-contiguous; outer dims
    may be strided since Q/K are views into the conv output)
  - ne00 (head_k_dim) % 32 == 0  (one simdgroup of reduction per row)

If supports_op returns false, the ggml scheduler falls back to the CPU
forward from 0004 — partial-Metal does not break correctness.

Equivalence verified by tests/unit/test_deltanet_pre_state.cpp on both
CPU and Metal backends within the F32 rounding floor (matches the
gated_delta_net upstream test's tolerance band: 1e-5 abs / 1e-4 rel).

Apply order: must be applied AFTER 0001/0002/0003/0004. apply-all.sh
enforces lexical order of patches/*.patch.

Files touched:
  ggml/src/ggml-metal/ggml-metal-impl.h     — kargs struct
  ggml/src/ggml-metal/ggml-metal-device.h   — pipeline-lookup decl
  ggml/src/ggml-metal/ggml-metal-device.cpp — pipeline-lookup impl
  ggml/src/ggml-metal/ggml-metal-device.m   — supports_op case
  ggml/src/ggml-metal/ggml-metal-ops.h      — op-fn decl
  ggml/src/ggml-metal/ggml-metal-ops.cpp    — dispatch case + op fn
  ggml/src/ggml-metal/ggml-metal.metal      — kernel_deltanet_pre_state_f32

